      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:2:57:2",
      "text": [
        " صِيَامُ ثَلَاثَةِ أَيَّامٍ فِي كَفَّارَةِ الْيَمِينِ مُتَتَابِعَاتٍ لَا يُفْصَلُ بَيْنَهُنَّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "And from him, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The Fasts of the three days regarding an expiation for the oath are consecutive, there cannot be a gap in between them’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. It is narrated from him (narrator of previous Hadith) from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hammad from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘The fast which is as expiation for an oath must be completed without any interval in between.’” "
        ]
      }
    }
